laboratory_examinations.findings: Elevated plasma IGF-I at 253 ng/ml (RR 54–161) and peaked at 1033 ng/ml (RR 223–972) during puberty.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Persistently elevated levels of plasma IGF-I throughout various ages.

laboratory_examinations.findings: GH levels high on spontaneous overnight sampling and stimulation with clonidine (peak 216 ng/ml).

laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Indicated relative insulin deficiency for ambient glucose levels.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Bone mineral content measured at 1.3 kg, low for lean tissue mass (SDS /H110022.9).
